title: Where love exists Chapter 27: New old friends
excerpt: She had forgotten, to be honest, that Jon and Theon had been friends of sorts. They weren’t close the way Robb and Theon were or the way Robb and Jon were. But they had a sort of friendly rivalry.

title: [NO SPOILERS]Terrible post-binge-watching blues
body:
I started watching about two weeks ago and finished season 7 yesterday and I just want to say GoT is insanely entertaining and addictive. I felt like I was literally living in Westeros. I did an all-night binge to finish season 7 and now I felt like shit and super super depressed like somebody dies in my life lol. Anyway GoT has set the bar really high and I don’t think I will be watching any shows on this same level for quite some time or maybe never.



Source: https://ift.tt/2J7wQes

title: [SPOILERS] Season 4 Episode 1
body:
I’ve been rewatching the series and the season 4 scene of Twyin melting down a sword just made me consider—he waited to melt down Ned’s sword until after Robb died. He thought Bran and Rickon were dead, and after Robb died every male Stark was to his knowledge dead. He never would have melted down their family sword until he knew their bloodline had ended, because he holds family to the highest precedence.



Source: https://ift.tt/2PKbPsW
